ALBUM REVIEW
The eighth studio album from the Canadian pop-punks, the follow-up to 2019's Order in Decline, and their debut for Rise Records, is also their epitaph -- they announced their disbandment after its release. A nod to the Black Sabbath album of the same name, it is split over two discs: one in their classic pop-punk vein, and the other in the heavy metal style.
